sentences.text: I will never forgive my friends for what they did last summer.
üò≠ My friend group, 'The Fab Five,' had been planning a big summer trip for months.
‚òÄÔ∏è We talked about it constantly in our group chat, sharing ideas for destinations and activities.
I was so excited, I'd even started saving up my allowance money.
üí∞ But then, a week before we were supposed to book everything, the group chat went silent.
Completely dead. ü¶ó I texted them individually.
My best friend, Chloe, said her family had a last-minute emergency.
Another friend, Liam, said he was grounded.

ü§î I felt like something was wrong, but I believed them.
I mean, why would they lie to me?
ü•∫ That Saturday, I was just scrolling through my phone, bored out of my mind.

It was a picture of all four of them‚Ä¶ on a beach in Hawaii.
üèùÔ∏è The caption read: 'Best trip with the best people!'
